INSERT INTO `helps` (`id`, `name`, `help_content`, `admin`) VALUES
(1, '1. Getting Started', '<p>If you are the first user of the system, please follow this section to complete the process of setting up accounts for yourself and the rest of the users.<br /><br />Since this will be the first time you are logging into the system, you will need to use an account that has been previously created by the developers. Please note that after you&rsquo;ve completed this setup, you will be asked to delete this account and use your own account.</p>\r\n<h2>1.1 Setting up your administrator account</h2>\r\n<p>Step 1:<br />Go to the website address(URL) that has been provided to you by the host (in this case is probably UBC IT). <br /><br />Step 2: <br />You should see a page similar to the one below. Please login with the following credentials.<br /><strong>Email Address</strong>: admin@cims.com<br /><strong>Password</strong>: r2d2c3po85<br /><img id="docs-internal-guid-c44a3040-663d-eb21-84f0-1c90b913f989" style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/aU5UxicoK9I8HlB_pcS_F6uOAAyjaM0UbUgeV8BWok0pJolLKBpZomuJTt4pXO8MK3zbTkaM_Vi5Nbrauu-TPLs3CL5hH7ogtCTraX28WyjLiXDVqM-qTrse3Sj23kI-MA" alt="" width="624px;" height="307px;" /><br /><br />Step 3:<br />You will be taken directly to the Home page which will not contain any ideas since this is the first time anyone has accessed the system. The first task is to create your own user. On the top of the page you will see a button that looks like this:</p>\r\n<p><img id="docs-internal-guid-c44a3040-663e-1e89-8176-3d0bf26d6fb7" style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/5ygkhImev3QhaKeDPIJNPHFtmg3IieDZX61JUmFheVvIlOmyhYNliOElkk6PHS4QJdyYKZrCAEJGKsCACZRGyV-ROeLU7XufXKJKLkbdDuCnMbuAHDn9X5rUuBlB1V7S_g" alt="management button.png" width="127px;" height="52px;" /><br />Click this button to show the drop-down list. Within this drop-down, please select <strong>User Management</strong>.</p>\r\n<p><img id="docs-internal-guid-c44a3040-663f-866d-a72b-dcdfb63ab413" style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/zKAcXE65v5_aeLq0nO_xrf-2rDttoWwY2XeyO808aj3VwN9uQflPYA-jBuhOK7sCxVdlfQMYf2rA7GsurcQcuXfGudxUIOL6UP_ZYPQ85dATroBt1sC_HnVPNR6ctQaCPw" alt="management button open.png" width="186px;" height="143px;" /><br />Step 4: <br />You should now be re-directed to the User Management page which should look similar to the picture below. If you are not redirected to this page, please attempt Step 3 again.<br /><br />&nbsp;<img id="docs-internal-guid-c44a3040-663f-b1c0-25f2-178c7ddf99de" style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/o1T2yf2FV8QkJLhh-D_mrEFooJUhJ4OfDOUnbo_moBHgVH3LzetIT0B0S_YkL-ekAW4uLroqb_hg0tIC924xxDNrpAtKGYtKOJYqi1QP5pYTe86gfMBjlqMix9McuRU7Cw" alt="" width="624px;" height="137px;" /><br /><br />Step 5: <br />It is time to create your own user. In the top right corner you should see an icon that looks like a person with a plus symbol, similar to this <img id="docs-internal-guid-c44a3040-663f-d6f8-0f8b-7ef41a9f7af4" style="border: none; transform: rotate(0.00rad); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad);" src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/1KkDBSlR3qePRqsUJQm_M46xymDqFbBIeOms3T4_wSr7EX7RZou9nqNIML9aUK9xf-gfaiYsdkch6x5bC__nbjaTNM02ESaf8WtJNhzF6PlHDa1m_MnwyCERt4EIRWb4Cg" alt="add a user.png" width="45px;" height="43px;" />. Please click this button.<br /><br /><br />Step 6: <br />You should now be re-directed to a <strong>Create User</strong> page, just like the image below. You will see 3 fields which you will need to fill in: Name, Email, and Role.</p>\r\n<p><img id="docs-internal-guid-c44a3040-6640-6c02-1c00-4d7043ab2910" style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-Bo3pFjUQWOwQXl0KnOjRba2CLvLkOCYdCqvFUfnAufExWJaCDnmKkPOQlNyPtJXZ2xxd8ZPb3C8VpAox5uCbhw9NG8qOvtVrtcWQ50esYarov0xd8ZhmxmBOHc3kzJ1Sg" alt="Create User.png" width="624px;" height="295px;" /><br /><strong>Name</strong>: This will be the display name of the user you are creating. <br /><strong>Email Address</strong>: You will be required to enter a valid email address. It is vital that you use a real email account as an email will be sent to that address with steps to create a password.<br /><strong>Role</strong>: There are 2 roles to select from. Since you are going to be an administrator of the system you need to select the Admin role. Standard user&rsquo;s will not have access to the management tools.<br />Once all 3 fields are filled out, please click the <strong>Submit</strong> button.<br /><br />Step 7: <br />You should now be directed back to the <strong>User Management</strong> page. You should now see 2 users of the system, the admin@cims.com and the account that you created. If you do not see the account you just created, please attempt Steps 4-6 again. If you continue to have problems, please contact your server host.<br /><br />Step 8: <br />Now that you&rsquo;ve create the new user, you want to logout of the admin@cims.com account. To do so, in the top right corner you should see the following button.</p>\r\n<p><img id="docs-internal-guid-c44a3040-6641-0e76-c1e1-e28f294695de" style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/ih-834RwqLiZXY6ck7Ullhl4cYP2lxcjTclM7_oIHqdwVX5AakL5p6MVIU_f44cEwjx7jFFQwaOs9o9I2LwKM0Lr_bhlOazYOH_OqX6seu4zL5DGh_pqOJLyjt_DNRV2lw" alt="Logout button.png" width="149px;" height="47px;" /><br />Please click this button and then select Logout. This should now take you back to the login page. <br /><br /><br />Step 9: <br />You should receive an email within a few minutes from no-reply@cims.com. The email should look similar to the one below. Inside this email will be a link. This link will direct you to a new page where you will setup your password for the account you just created. The link will only be valid for a period of 24 hours for security reasons. Please click the link.</p>\r\n<p><img id="docs-internal-guid-c44a3040-6641-633d-35ba-53b4ff381be6" style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/X9a3z4XhgKTA-MOKUg6igKi2V81ZhKADioFAUU9g49zs7DEhromUcbWb-jS-2U7CwVca-qN-rlNjsac-zNPHZV5yfwebEkkg7n7nk4wo_Ha6hDNHifHAYfCwvXquIceMLQ" alt="" width="449px;" height="141px;" /><br /><br />Step 10:<br />You should now be at the New Password page that looks like the image below. This page contains 1 field that you are required to fill out: your new password. This password must be between 8 to 32 characters in length. Once you&rsquo;ve entered your password, please click Submit. <br /><br /><img id="docs-internal-guid-c44a3040-6641-84d5-7c83-30f47e3c82c8" style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/r8ZhNh557FjnNA5CKaq4ryKJhBD23pitUxkwvWHzuKo9iTosAXJYah3reJPEmtok4c8yoMbIwSgS1erOzmDrR9eB7h2qKsw7VmL2oNg4ULz8m8P5JgnjZOzoeaRwWISw0A" alt="" width="367px;" height="188px;" /><br />Step 11:&nbsp; <br />You should now be re-directed back to the login page. Please login with the user you just created (<strong>not</strong> the admin@cims.com account you used earlier). If the setup process worked, you should be logged in and taken to the <strong>Home</strong> page once again. If this does not work, there are 2 solutions.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; height: 456px;" width="529">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Solution A. Please repeat the steps to log back in with admin@cims.com and proceed back to <strong>User Management</strong> to ensure the new user was created and the email address is correct.<br /><br />Solution B. The password you are attempting may be different than the one created. To fix this you can reset the password. On the login page you should see a link that looks similar to this:</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><img id="docs-internal-guid-c44a3040-6642-5c8d-f067-150d01d321e1" style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/NB1axYTot-Sm213vtetDewOZwoXn7hrZOVfHCxRMJLQkGs8wrTCFXFbEaOtRLPm4cLmrT9nKNhDlgZCCX8gSOSSTNXzYefvNW43bFPaTcHJpwxfbjyrw40Mt5wUVE01yIQ" alt="Forgot password.png" width="137px;" height="33px;" /><br />Click this link and you will be re-directed to the Reset Password page (seen in the image below). It will ask you to provide your email address, please enter the email address you are using for this system, then click <strong>Reset Password</strong> button. From here, follow Steps 9 and 10 again.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><br /><img id="docs-internal-guid-c44a3040-6642-86fe-6acb-7ab4e9716fc0" style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/pcAemh3za4FnLVMnuaNZTFE-hUvkp1K8vVBqqZKZUBwLZgMw2UtFFtdnN1aFPQopWrj6I5h3uweT7Wf-wy7RPPfpEYuRtVWJ9KZDfWFHfAMDwXT6gzUoFwU13GqTSNbLxw" alt="" width="368px;" height="202px;" /></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><br /><br style="text-align: center;" /><br />You&rsquo;ve now successfully logged into your own account! The next section will describe the removal of the admin@cims.com account. This account should be removed after you&rsquo;ve created your own account, however, please only do so once you feel confident that you&rsquo;ve correctly setup the first user. <br /><br /></p>\r\n<h2>1.2 Removing the admin@cims.com account</h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;After you&rsquo;ve successfully created your own account, we should remove the admin@cims.com account as it is no longer required. Follow the steps below to complete this.<br /><br />Step 1: <br />Please login with your account that should have administrator privileges. <br /><br />Step 2: <br />You will be taken to the Home page. On the top you will see a button that looks like this:</p>\r\n<p><img id="docs-internal-guid-c44a3040-6668-aae6-5bd5-e49e59ec1c67" style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/2crG4x1uLzLR3d4ZPr29sLMnnzSGGR1TsFChIj3-2TClAzlrLtjOS2nkDM7zgQ-OIliZuX6mEb0vpjmP_BlHId8oaEiiMtp4MCstPW1LKifC1Cwe2b_JWcwbfqVcT3XmCg" alt="management button.png" width="127px;" height="52px;" /><br />Click this button to show the drop-down list. Inside this drop-down, please select <strong>User Management</strong>.</p>\r\n<p><img id="docs-internal-guid-c44a3040-6668-c94f-4b92-6a5bc20ad43a" style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/REKro9sfk_N4YlbQfoQ-UGAR53norYeF_eK9SdTweCibhDoj5NBZ-IvWMQ1qYFl8aBI0ckbp93g6BONMRKBH27N1LZ2eVy5A6h7U6_TI4_816nnkod_tyLCOQ_XsC9rHIA" alt="management button open.png" width="186px;" height="143px;" /><br /><br />Step 3: <br />You should now be re-directed to the User Management page which should look similar to the picture below. If you are not redirected to this page, please attempt Step 2 again.<br /><br />&nbsp;<img id="docs-internal-guid-c44a3040-6668-f60f-4e2e-2103d3211d4c" style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/d8nM5XiJw9cJgxkMgmbpBlYOuLpd4-mNiNBOxlRwKPTs9IfYMDPl8kj9wXQ1SmSdZRhy3-YQG19b7XRsfr3v0inUrvq25uBPFXcQv8O86yfiw7q_VhZU0jrwP9cclVlByQ" alt="" width="624px;" height="116px;" /><br />&nbsp;<br />Step 4:<br />Please locate the Admin user. It should have the follow properties<br /><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Name</strong>: Admin<br /><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Email Address</strong>: admin@cims.com<br />There should be a section labeled <strong>Actions</strong>. You want to remove this account from the system. To do so, there will be a icon that resembles a trash can.</p>\r\n<p><img id="docs-internal-guid-c44a3040-6669-778a-079a-81171300077e" style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/SVwsx6dvtsCK4Ltu0JBXBfBJECYn_fx5zczIzRgIpTKOWA6QAdOCWg5L_BcTMLuV552CM5c38-yspe9GS7-WfvcfrlRZL3JU92wFcM8QgwbLFJsBimT92vT_6wAmILtktg" alt="Delete button.png" width="184px;" height="78px;" /><br /><br />If you hover over this icon it should say &ldquo;Delete&rdquo;. Please click this icon.<br /><br />Step 5:<br />You should now be shown a prompt asking if you are sure you want to delete this user (as shown in the image below). <strong>Please make sure it says &ldquo;Admin&rdquo; and not another user</strong>. You&nbsp; only need to delete the admin@cims.com at this time. Please click the <strong>Delete User</strong> button.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img id="docs-internal-guid-c44a3040-6669-ab07-7853-7addbd350de1" style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/atAwTcOqY74TcjsJkLt8qNeBgq7C6T_leVcrD9j0VULIFWI2f3A907gpWW3Op9auyuCMOqIYvceDov0Ry2WfHnzdxhFj0bkx7eDDKJq8rUIGidt_-eVNDPnj8QXEwBmcWw" alt="are you sure delete user.png" width="395px;" height="159px;" /><br />The admin@cims.com user should now be removed from the system and now longer be displayed on the User Management page. If this is not the case, please attempt Steps 4 and 5 again. If these do not work, please contact your server host.<br /><br /></p>', 1),
(2, '2. First Time Users', '<h2>2.1 Logging in</h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Step 1:<br />If you have not already had a user account set up for you, please talk to one of the administrators of the system to create you an account. If you are an administrator reading this, please go to the Create User section of the User Documentation.<br /><br />Step 2:<br />After setting up your account with the administrator you should receive an email within a few minutes from no-reply@cims.com. The email should look similar to the one below. Inside this email will be a link. This link will direct you to a new page where you will setup your password for the account just created for you. If you attempt to use this link after 24 hours it will be invalid for security reasons. Please click the link.</p>\r\n<p><strong id="docs-internal-guid-9f17b33b-6bdb-ee8e-da33-e4c08129963e" style="font-weight: normal;"><img style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/MzB3vPVukmyIJOycK-zbycIwNkOKu01o6PYkYe8aoIe-1Sm5bR1eTIAI-o-01tRZYg7qfxpvQg5H1YKFmQUFOmHuZVqcS8_uaLh1iR3UvckyWcPs23oCDD8Laiwh1XqF2g" alt="" width="449px;" height="141px;" /></strong><br /><br />Step 3:<br />You should now be at the New Password page that looks like the image below. On this page is 1 field in which you are required to fill out, your new password. This password must be between 8 to 32 characters in length. Once you&rsquo;ve added your password, please click <strong>Submit</strong>. <br /><br /><strong id="docs-internal-guid-9f17b33b-6bdc-1127-73ab-3250c5609007" style="font-weight: normal;"><img style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/dkjdz7-7hF9W0ePUtPKjA0M5a7qlQQsPGnjpH2lus3UP2_28FFKX6xSxQaT-At5dN1PEB16ldu_W_djQ1JiCn9sk-F_5eTkAgox9QGAqO41jiSWICp5jDh5By4G8sGAVmQ" alt="" width="367px;" height="188px;" /></strong><br /><br />Step 4: <br />You should now be re-directed back to the login page which looks like the image below.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong id="docs-internal-guid-9f17b33b-6bdc-2dd3-1a90-cd9ff309a612" style="font-weight: normal;"><img style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/aU5UxicoK9I8HlB_pcS_F6uOAAyjaM0UbUgeV8BWok0pJolLKBpZomuJTt4pXO8MK3zbTkaM_Vi5Nbrauu-TPLs3CL5hH7ogtCTraX28WyjLiXDVqM-qTrse3Sj23kI-MA" alt="" width="624px;" height="307px;" /></strong><br />Please login with your user. You will have to fill out the <strong>Email Address</strong> and <strong>Password</strong> fields. If the setup process worked, you should be taken to the application. If this does not work, there are 2 solutions.</p>\r\n<table style="height: 426px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" width="732">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="text-align: left;">a. The password you are attempting may be different than the one created. To fix this you can reset the password. On the login page you should see a link that looks similar to this:<strong id="docs-internal-guid-9f17b33b-6bdc-5961-0fe6-8d2ea144dc97" style="font-weight: normal;"><img style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/NB1axYTot-Sm213vtetDewOZwoXn7hrZOVfHCxRMJLQkGs8wrTCFXFbEaOtRLPm4cLmrT9nKNhDlgZCCX8gSOSSTNXzYefvNW43bFPaTcHJpwxfbjyrw40Mt5wUVE01yIQ" alt="Forgot password.png" width="137px;" height="33px;" /></strong><br />Click this link and you will be re-directed to the <strong>Reset Password</strong> page (seen in the image below). It will ask you to give the email address, please enter the one you are attempting to login as then click Reset Password. From here, follow Steps 10 and 11 again.<br /><strong id="docs-internal-guid-9f17b33b-6bdc-8311-42b9-aa4c05ad66d7" style="font-weight: normal;"><img style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/AZPlEVGK_YLfavJOof_yG8w6_2YDNRWcjHs2AcS3lyanb1a_54Jg78YJjfAgA_6Eh7JYUgUQVCXTjDgAdkbfpb5FH_HWwhaE4L5HuurElHAzXXOt9sqYLNcMAJX0wMKXmg" alt="Screen Shot 2014-04-03 at 9.11.50 PM.png" width="525px;" height="252px;" /></strong><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />b. Talk to your administrator to make sure that they have setup your account with the correct email address.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><br /><br /><br />You&rsquo;ve now successfully logged into your new account! The next sections will explain the general overviews of the <strong>Home</strong> page, <strong>Search</strong> page, and <strong>My Page</strong>, as well as workflows that may be required of you to use features of this system such as <strong>Adding an Idea</strong>, <strong>Searching for Ideas</strong>, or <strong>Managing your Ideas</strong>.<br /><br />Step 5: <br />If you want to logout in the top right corner you should see the following button.</p>\r\n<p><strong id="docs-internal-guid-9f17b33b-6bdd-895c-2cbc-4e450fd79e98" style="font-weight: normal;"><img style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/ih-834RwqLiZXY6ck7Ullhl4cYP2lxcjTclM7_oIHqdwVX5AakL5p6MVIU_f44cEwjx7jFFQwaOs9o9I2LwKM0Lr_bhlOazYOH_OqX6seu4zL5DGh_pqOJLyjt_DNRV2lw" alt="Logout button.png" width="149px;" height="47px;" /></strong><br />&nbsp;<br />Please click this button and then select <strong>Logout</strong>. This should now take you back to the login page.</p>', 0),
(3, '3. General Overview', '<p>This section will give you an overview of the application. Contained here are descriptions of the different sections and interactions that can be found throughout the application. If you are looking for the steps required to complete certain task, you will want to look at Section 4 - Workflows of the document.<br /><br />Below is what the application looks like upon first logging in. At the top of the page you will see a navigation bar with links to the <strong>Home</strong> page, <strong>Search</strong> page and <strong>My Page</strong>, an <strong>Add Idea</strong> button,a <strong>Welcome Message</strong>, and a <strong>Notification</strong> button, all shown below. Each of these items will be discussed in further detail in sections below.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p><strong id="docs-internal-guid-9f17b33b-6be5-cab5-ed06-77fe812b54fe" style="font-weight: normal;"><img style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/lYRRGlEtwDp1RJLsjUJ7SDL7ezKBDSVw0j-7iFoGO1Pt4ZTN4nBvAn5mXQQPAL1rW5K7Dmkfh4Uf2POU5341mIZk572sH9pkSmARXgXXt8Q25UuepmikQqgC-h4rTta4xg" alt="" width="624px;" height="297px;" /></strong></p>\r\n<h2>3.1 Ideas</h2>\r\n<p>Throughout all sections of this document we will be referring to both small idea views and large idea views. These are fundamental to how you will be managing ideas for CCEL.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>3.1.1 Small Idea View</h3>\r\n<table style="height: 23px;" width="1120">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Located on the Home, Search, and My Page you will see what will be referred to as a Small Idea View, which is shown in the image to the right. These contain very brief information about an idea so you can get a general sense of what an idea is about. In order, a Small Idea view contains the following information:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Idea&rsquo;s Name</li>\r\n<li>Description</li>\r\n<li>Status</li>\r\n<li>Owner</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>As well, there is a page icon which is used for tracking ideas (explained in <em>Section 3.4 - My Page</em>). You can click one of these ideas which will open a new window which we&rsquo;ve called <strong>Large Idea View</strong>, explained in the section below.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td><strong id="docs-internal-guid-9f17b33b-6be7-5e0f-24d0-777ada257dcc" style="font-weight: normal;"><img style="border: none; transform: rotate(0.00rad); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad);" src="https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/ulQCY3sIL6bSLf2wK7h_UbR-dDTPDWyennfpwTmwMSH989zi9tndQc0_8-ARLGidEnQzeKxC1EldgXdR4bgoLqY4MCFp4IJgL7y5nDRdhheJoMwQnNPz4QGs6mbTrhbfLA" alt="small idea view.png" width="203px;" height="235px;" /></strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>3.1.2 Large Idea View</h3>\r\n<p>Here contains all the information about a given idea. The <strong>Large Idea View</strong> will be your source for managing, sharing, and communicating about an idea.<br /><strong id="docs-internal-guid-9f17b33b-6be9-6fde-efbe-4e98453270f5" style="font-weight: normal;"><img style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/m7QlkbCfsFy2qAQpmrw7QFQ8ANDvg64hNXmi8VIOJsy9qOOos0ll7bxf9-5qKxOG1PNY6sYrLDz4_zUNPkUYBKmXQGS983ZKA8Ig3kMm01-cJMXnj6L7CKa77KpTmQKmow" alt="" width="624px;" height="372px;" /></strong>We will now break down what information we have shown with our large idea:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Idea Name</strong>: Name of the idea given by a member of CCEL<br /><strong>Community Partner</strong>: Name of the community partner organization for which the idea is from.<br /><strong>Contact Name</strong>: Name of the contact person at the community partner organization.<br /><strong>Contact Details</strong>: Email address and/or phone number of the contact person at the community partner organization.<br /><strong>Description</strong>: Full description of the idea as given by the contact person at the community organization.<br /><strong>Timeframe</strong>: The start or end date of an idea. If no dates are specified the Timeframe field will be displayed as flexible.<br /><strong>Type</strong>: Give a general sense of the kind of idea this might be - from a one-time project to an on-going activity.<br /><strong>Program Referral</strong>: Even at an early stage in an idea''s development, there may be a clear connection to a Centre program or CBEL opportunity that you may know of.<br /><strong>Organization Mandate</strong>: The categories that describe the mandate of the organization that has proposed this idea.<br /><strong>Focus Area</strong>: The categories that describe the community priority area that the project/placement hopes to address. This might be the same or different from the organization''s mandate.<br /><strong>Main Activities</strong>: The categories that best describe the main activities that would be done in this placement/project.<br /><strong>Delivery Location</strong>: The location(s) where the project/placement would take place.<br /><strong>Disciplines</strong>: Any faculties/departments/disciplines that this idea is best suited for.<br /><strong>Current Status</strong>: The status of this idea.<br /><strong>Owner</strong>: The current person responsible for managing the idea. Please refer to Section 3.4 - My Page for further explanation.<br /><strong>Referenced ideas</strong>: The ideas related to a specific idea. Please refer to Section 3.8 - Referred Ideas for further explanation.<br /><strong>Comments</strong>: A communication about an idea made by CCEL members. Please refer to Section 3.6 - Commenting on an Idea for further explanation.<br /><strong>Share</strong>: A way to share the current idea with a member of CCEL. Please refer to Section - 3.7 Sharing an Idea for further explanation.</p>\r\n<h2><br /><br />3.2 Home</h2>\r\n<p>When logging into the website, you will be sent to the Home page. You will see that the Home page is broken down into four sections.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<h4>Active Ideas</h4>\r\n<p>These are ideas that have the latest activity. Activity is defined as an idea being updated or commented on. On each of the small idea views, you will notice there is a colour on the bottom of them. This signifies activity. Ideas with a very bright green will be active ideas. As ideas become more inactive, this colour will change from bright green to a purplish blue, as seen in the image below.</p>\r\n<p><strong id="docs-internal-guid-9f17b33b-6bec-2549-2443-37c84da4e494" style="font-weight: normal;"><img style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/9hDT1hfPH_cTir7WiWyN_hmjZPz211lN1s3USWPb3I2Qj0jEKVvl7NKo-GQxN51uNDJsnHLrG42O32wZSFieqIor2Ain88FA-kOEuOuyH7VFzVgJOa970HfK3IhKIswUdA" alt="" width="624px;" height="184px;" /></strong></p>\r\n<h4>Recently Created Ideas</h4>\r\n<p>This section contains the ideas that were most recently created by members of CCEL.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<h4>Community Partner Ideas</h4>\r\n<p>Ideas that were created using the public page (created by community partners) will be displayed in this section in order of most recently added.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<h4>Inactive Ideas</h4>\r\n<p>This section is the opposite of active ideas, being the most inactive ideas. These will be ideas with the blue colour at the bottom of them. An idea will be the max blue colour after 30 days of inactivity.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><br /><br />3.3 Search</h2>\r\n<p>The Search page allows you to quickly find any idea in the system. There are 3 major functionalities on the Search page: searching, filtering, and sorting. This section gives a brief description of the purpose of each of these functionalities. For a full explanation of <strong>searching</strong>, <strong>filtering</strong>, and <strong>sorting</strong> please refer to <em>Sections 4.6, 4.7, and 4.8</em></p>\r\n<p><strong id="docs-internal-guid-9f17b33b-6bec-4f76-353d-3de108e819db" style="font-weight: normal;"><img style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/Gkh6SMb1gH37yFOU_QsA4awqG-i0uDMgQFKLcRAhlXFRi1VqevmHgfvhEoQZG11WjDdp-FjDUlqzEdBzHsaRAyzQ9X6KvLQP8zII5UumeRljHVSm8qOQR5riwOPxGnkAsg" alt="" width="624px;" height="487px;" /></strong><br />Searching allows you to find ideas in the system that have information matching specified keywords. This is especially useful for you to find ideas that you already know something about, because you can search by the name of the idea. It is also useful to find ideas that are for a specific Community Partner, or have a specific Contact person.<br /><br />Filtering allows you to filter the current list of ideas to only contain ideas with certain owners or category values. This is especially useful if you do not know the exact idea you are searching for.&nbsp; For example, if you needed to find projects for Computer Science students you would filter down to ideas with their Discipline set to Department of Computer Science.<br /><br />Sorting allows you to sort the current list of ideas by a specific value. This is useful if you want to sort alphabetically, or you want to find out which ideas are the most active.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><br />3.4 My Page</h2>\r\n<p>My Page contains all the ideas related to you in two sections: Ideas you own and Ideas you are tracking. These sections are resembled the same way as shown in the Home page. Any idea that you see in this section will be the ideas that you receive notifications about when they are updated or commented on (explained in <em>Section 3.5 - Notifications</em>).<br /><strong id="docs-internal-guid-9f17b33b-6bed-d954-5a60-b42e5320a0ed" style="font-weight: normal;"><img style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/_lpBijbglnjI51gxws2YO_W4enJMwOLg8hbX0Vs_rV_LqSWrdE_BUsVArtylR406aJwbp6DgyoNDqk73txmy5v4NXJF44xwTjmbmbZ5VUStvlzqp6eWONMOS36ixg8vN1w" alt="" width="624px;" height="353px;" /></strong></p>\r\n<h4>Ideas you own</h4>\r\n<p>There 2 different ways that ideas will end up in this section. Whenever you first create an idea, it will be defaulted to you as the owner of the idea unless you specify otherwise. Secondly, if any member CCEL updates an idea&rsquo;s owner to you, the idea will also then be shown in this section.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<h4>Ideas you are tracking</h4>\r\n<p>What we mean by tracking an idea is giving you the ability to follow the progress of any idea in the system, even if you are not the owner of it. You will notice that on all ideas is a page icon with is either blue or white. Blue symbolizes an untracked idea, while white is a tracked idea. At anyone point you can click these icons to switch between tracking and untracking.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong id="docs-internal-guid-9f17b33b-6bef-096e-2dae-b57358b24f8d" style="font-weight: normal;"><img style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/00LXCivmDg-e0C4GG17QkoekZSkfnNK-qMO54BbNLYki_imhlDDxeXd2C-WzPlP3zZ-aQCjJCvyh5R84nf7ZmTSp5xK3nJys9oJdGomWIHMcmRxs9zJk0vekGZ56whB7kA" alt="" width="480px;" height="233px;" /></strong><strong> Untracked&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Tracked</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>3.5 Notifications</h2>\r\n<p>There is a bell icon located in the top right of the screen next to the Welcome button. This is where all your notifications will be located. You will receive notifications from ideas that you are either the owner of or that you are tracking, both of which are explained in <em>Section 3.4 - My Page</em>. Anytime a CCEL member shares an idea with you (explained in <em>Section 3.7 - Sharing an idea</em>) or comments on an idea you own or are tracking (explained in <em>Section 3.6 - Commenting on an idea</em>), you will receive a notification. The number of unread notifications that you currently have will be shown within the red circle that overlays the bell icon. Unread notifications will be first, highlighted in blue, with read notifications underneath them, unhighlighted. <br /><br />To check your notifications do the following:<br />Step 1: <br />Click the bell icon on the top right corner of the navbar as shown below.<br /><br />Step 2: <br />Click on the highlighted idea to view the new notification<br /><strong id="docs-internal-guid-9f17b33b-6bf0-4fbd-b58b-38c0aef35ee0" style="font-weight: normal;"><img style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/vHGHpZ6yVXT5pa393AXwhnZ8yEntyeilEvidRc1-8_YdgOaOnZ3AcWu_WErVj0NEbeGW8Z9csaqpMgCS6tR2X9OnDrtMRFH_-JVVYN9N78A1pEYTXoK0xtSe396vcA6f_w" alt="Screen Shot 2014-04-03 at 9.43.32 PM.png" width="624px;" height="193px;" /></strong></p>\r\n<h2>3.6 Commenting on an Idea</h2>\r\n<p>To ensure you can maintain an open communication about an idea, each <strong>Large Idea View</strong> (explained in <em>Section 3.1 - Ideas</em>) contains a way of leaving a comment. These comments will be shown with the newest comment at the top and show the name, date and time that comments were made. Whenever a comment is made, the owner and anyone who is tracking the idea will receive a notification (explained in <em>Section 3.5 - Notifications</em>).<br /><br />To make a comment, follow the steps below:<br />Step 1:&nbsp; <br />Click on the editable dialogue box that have the words <strong>Leave a comment</strong> and type the desired message.<br /><br />Step 2: <br />Click the <strong>Comment</strong> button below the Leave a comment dialogue to view your comment on the <strong>Comments</strong> feed above. This will also clear the dialog box so you can type another message.<br /><br /><strong id="docs-internal-guid-9f17b33b-6bf2-c13e-09e6-b05704f4b905" style="font-weight: normal;"><img style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/Qke6MswOvtJ8V0j_vT1Uvyp-RrMctGelqp74URkUW-_Gg1FJ7iMd3-Ohs9JXFODRmOABoexg1nVbTNvxgYJQrMI9menvMvhOJUPKTNEwMoycAEKZc_EsQYgAONXyIX289w" alt="" width="624px;" height="308px;" /></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>3.7 Sharing an Idea</h2>\r\n<p>If you believe that another user of the application would be interested in an idea that you are currently look at, you can <strong>Share</strong> the idea. Sharing will send a notification (explained in <em>Section 3.5 - Notifications</em>) with a message stating that you&rsquo;ve shared this idea with them.<br />&nbsp; <br />To share an idea, follow the steps below:<br />Step 1: <br />Click on the editable dialogue box that have the words &ldquo;Share with others&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p><strong id="docs-internal-guid-9f17b33b-6bf3-e765-3a43-ec9f2ed17de6" style="font-weight: normal;"><img style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/jLAm_J1h0jmxtzjZMO00wPm6t-VXAUH34KJGb4-agOMDAfIBmXZc9AnNzl1hgwxAahmY2CL0LZY_PH6PuFxIauAol9vDzcUsqzNHbB7L_EFodmq_6wzA_1yKxERA5KPApw" alt="" width="624px;" height="80px;" /></strong><br /><br />Step 2: Click the user you wish you share the idea with. You can repeat this process for any amount of users you wish to share the idea with.</p>\r\n<p><strong id="docs-internal-guid-9f17b33b-6bf4-038b-4d56-61ffbcf02ffd" style="font-weight: normal;"><img style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/CteWlE5naECqduwd-wgsdcNajxpMKKcnpybqfz6cL7NO9sbO48t5e22-9FFfGVqSsAStYHa92nfT-UBs2_Xohist2ComIuQjV71rhUvfu-xDjxrz8HIWHvYGulEkUfKmaA" alt="" width="624px;" height="236px;" /></strong><br /><br />Step 3:<br />Click the <strong>Share</strong> button to view a confirmation window stating you shared the idea<br /><br />Step 4: <br />Click <strong>Ok</strong> to close the confirmation window</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>3.8 Referred Ideas</h2>\r\n<p>There may be times when ideas will be similar to each other, or an idea may be a parent of a select number of ideas. To show this relationship, we can setup referred ideas when we create or update ideas. When doing either of these tasks, you will see a section similar to the image below.</p>\r\n<p><strong id="docs-internal-guid-9f17b33b-6bf4-f09e-c8b0-f030298a2457" style="font-weight: normal;"><img style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/cLQ4aoH2sZ3FBSN7q_jZdu6TFsOk5_leotEmfHiRRsc4WbuEbq22pT86v11VGRTXmonWB0jiF9OBpKPJOTccL4KZJKNagOM7JNZp-1FugRqmfU6vlEnhepdrPpfZxNEgkQ" alt="" width="624px;" height="37px;" /></strong></p>\r\n<p>If you click into this box, you will see it is populated with all the ideas. Select the idea that you wish to refer to. You may select more than 1 idea to refer to as well.</p>\r\n<p><strong id="docs-internal-guid-9f17b33b-6bf5-37ef-969c-7ba036619e8a" style="font-weight: normal;"><img style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/1o86_DvbBHRDC1yj74GARMZoHuTPBRRJb0YgZeI48zzoXSHPlbQS8zyyCSpEY1TezNE1diL75Xbm9JMsz9pALwp0iew3we11uR_H77Ji2B4WubtHcG95fm66bdhaEL_Xsg" alt="" width="624px;" height="144px;" /></strong><br /><br />Now when you go back to the idea that you set up the references for, you will see a list of all the ideas you referred to. These are also set up as a link, therefore if you clicked on one of the referred ideas, you will be taken to that idea.</p>\r\n<p><strong id="docs-internal-guid-9f17b33b-6bf5-5b4f-f156-66cdce11f7f8" style="font-weight: normal;"><img style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/bsNhVkbVWQj74rLtTJf0aDFv3SANOkvG5sDFTH-su-H13GFxEgeBcW5pVb31KPcKX1uUQEF5SFKUa6idYkUXLGW1efjJYWvH5BnusnNAs3sxouJm8gd4-PEyTWlH5RGubg" alt="" width="329px;" height="70px;" /></strong></p>', 0),
(4, '4. Workflows  -  4.1 Adding ideas', '<p>One of the main purposes of the application is to create ideas. This section will explain the process of how a user would add an idea to the system. If you are wondering how a Community Partner can add an idea, please refer to <em>Section 4.5 - Community Partner Ideas</em>.<br />&nbsp;<br />Step 1: <br />In the top right corner of all pages in the application, you will see a button called <strong>Add Idea</strong>, which looks like this:</p>\r\n<p><span id="docs-internal-guid-c44a3040-e8a4-a805-af94-be1ac956724e" style="font-size: 15px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;"><img style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/WD2bD_PYTKKDgZGXMSWq3I3C52oMFlQ2DQOZm1B5lfZ03vZFYagjIu9QLtU_2GrbWBoPg48IJ5dryZDEG0ZY76JAkZU9NaiGtPNy6fX1fpA3Dr0tAKrnP8gBaJBCXnblMg" alt="add idea button.png" width="112px;" height="51px;" /></span><br />Please click this button.<br /><br />Step 2:&nbsp; <br />A new window will appear titled <strong>Add a New Idea</strong> and look like the image below.<br /><br /><span id="docs-internal-guid-c44a3040-e8a4-dd62-e196-987f19a49d52" style="font-size: 15px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;"><img style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/dfRQLEKx0zsNgJGZ9K9H7dbfLiwyPzEaj1lGx4HKgTy7hchySB-wv8cQ3X_iBz0k_TatlH6x5f-olvRvkIHaRUUg3ddm2RsJc_knRmQ_zAYm0jiMVSGk_0VmMqJ3oQNABg" alt="add idea modal.png" width="624px;" height="297px;" /></span><br />Step 3:<br />Inside this new window will be a list of text fields and drop-down values for which you will use to bring your idea to life. Refer to <em>Appendix A.1 - Description of Idea Fields</em> for details about the fields.<br /><br /><br />The minimum fields required to add a new idea are:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Name</li>\r\n<li>Contact Name</li>\r\n<li>Contact Email</li>\r\n<li>Description</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: You will notice as you are selecting values for categories that there are 3 different ways of doing so.</p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;"><strong>Single-Select</strong>: This is used for Type, Status and Owner fields. It will only allow you to select 1 value for anyone of these fields.<br /><strong>Multi-Select</strong>:&nbsp; For categories that are not single-select, they will be multi-select. This means that for each category you can select zero to many different values. To do so, click the field for the category you wish to assign, find the value and then click it. To add another value, just simple do the same process again.<br /><strong>Specific Values</strong>: For many of the multi-selects, if one of the values does not fit into what you believe the value should be, you can specify a value. To do so, click inside the text field, type the value you wish to use and it should appear at the top of the list. Once you are satisfied with the value, click it to add it to the list.</p>\r\n<p><span id="docs-internal-guid-c44a3040-e8a6-6aed-f721-e78bdda10912" style="font-size: 15px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;"><img style="transform: rotate(0rad); display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/eXBPMHzL1qAWhbndhgYajalW2062agX4hF2x3_ep8yTKeC8hJ0OyvcRpoXoyBHgHPX0hEKg6MRKd9UequBhNl5i-OhO9NTVtbSliDgb5ROxU0bqmfzQOgUttiFrPBNr6Xw" alt="specified value.png" width="555px;" height="247px;" /></span><br />Step 4: <br />Once you have filled out all the information, click the <strong>Submit</strong> button at the bottom right of the new window and the new idea will be added to the system. This idea will be displayed in the Recently Created Ideas section of the Home page (explained in <em>Section 3.2 - Home page</em>), as well as the Owned ideas section of the My Page (explained in <em>Section 3.4 - My Page</em>) of the owner (by default, this is the person that created the idea). <br /><br /></p>', 0);
